Brooke Anderson has been appointed as Chief of Staff and Counselor for the National Security Staff at the White House. She has extensive experience in the public policy arena, having worked at the White House National Security Council, the U.S. Department of Energy, and in the nonprofit and private sector. Anderson also served as Chief of Staff and Counselor to Ambassador Susan E. Rice. She has focused on UN Security Council matters, including UN peacekeeping missions and nonproliferation, while serving as Ambassador and Alternate Representative for Special Political Affairs at the U.S. Mission to the United Nations. Anderson graduated from Sarah Lawrence College.